                        <interp inst="t18401019-name-1136" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN STOWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am constable of the Southampton railway. I re<lb></lb>ceived charge of the prisoner on Friday evening last, October the 23rd, about twelve o'clock, in the waiting-room at the railway. I found on him ninety-seven sovereigns in this bag, and three sovereigns and some other money, this gold watch, a brace of pistols loaded, his old-coat, waistcoat, and trow<lb></lb>sers, and a variety of new wearing apparel in this carpet bag—he had come up by the last train from Southampton.</p>
